<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4544457>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 18. Nephochaetopteryx marianae Dodge, 1968, male terminalia. Holotype from Canal Zone, Barro Colorado Island, Panama (WSU). A. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. B. Cerci, dorsal view (setation omitted on the right side). C. Pregonite, lateral view; arrow showing grooves and granulations. D. Postgonite, lateral view. E. Sternite 5, ventral view (setation omitted on the left side). F. Phallus, lateral view; red arrow showing large, rounded projection of vesica and black arrow showing claw-like projection of ventral margin of distiphallus. Abbreviations: bp = basiphallus; dp = distiphallus; ip = inner process of vesica; ls = lateral stylus; ms = median stylus; ve = vesica. Scale bars: A, B, E = 0.1 mm; C, D, F = 0.05 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4544457/files/figure.png" .

